  little effort has been made to compare them systematically. Yet, such a
  comparison is crucial: existing discrepancies in the extent of unconscious
  processing inferred from these two techniques must be reconciled, as our
  understanding of unconscious vision should be independent of the technique
  used to prevent visibility. Here, we studied similarities and differences
