  buffer. This component is capable of holding up to around four episodic
  chunks, and is a valuable but essentially passive storage system, controlled
  by the central executive and accessible to conscious awareness. The
  multicomponent model has been systematically developed using a number of
  experimental tools. These include, principally, similarity effects to identify
  the type of coding involved, concurrent task methods to assess the
  contributions of the various subsystems to complex tasks, and
