  expose errors in their work or may produce conclusions that contradict their
  own. However, these hypotheses have not previously been studied
  systematically. METHODS AND FINDINGS: We related the reluctance to share
  research data for reanalysis to 1148 statistically significant results
  reported in 49 papers published in two major psychology journals. We found the
