  one of the most influential approaches for studying unconscious visual
  processing. In the b-CFS paradigm unconscious processing is inferred from the
  time different stimuli need to overcome CFS and break into awareness. A large
  body of literature using b-CFS now suggests that the extent of unconscious
  processing is greater than previously thought. Although b-CFS is widely
